
                                        ReadMe

Installation:

1) Down load the project from GITHUB
2)Open Terminal and navigate to your project WeatherApp.
3) If you haven't already done so, run this command:
sudo gem install cocoapods
Wait for it to finish before proceeding.
4) pod install



Description of the Application:

This is a simple weather application. It utilizes Swift CoreData, TableView, Google place and calling to Rest services.


How to use:
Simply type in the name of the city on the search bar on top with the magnifying glass.
You can select as many as 15 cities and click on the record and the weather for the city should display.
